		<span class="sys-font-heading3 sys-rhp-color-title">Administrator options</span><br />
	        <br>
			<div class="8pt">

			Advanced users and administrators can get more updates at the following Web sites.<br /><br />

			<a name="drivers"></a>
			<b>Windows Update Catalog</b><br />
			Windows Update Catalog provides a searchable collection of updates that can be installed on servers and other computers running Windows operating systems.<br /><br />
			<a target = "_top" class='sys-link-normal' href = http://v4.windowsupdate.microsoft.com/catalog/> http://v4.windowsupdate.microsoft.com/catalog/ </a> <br /><br />
	
			<a name="software"></a>
			<b>Microsoft Software Update Services (SUS) </b><br />
			Using SUS, administrators can install the latest high priority updates on servers running Windows 2000 or Windows Server 2003, and computers running Windows 2000 Professional or Windows XP Professional, inside their corporate firewall.<br /><br />
			<a target = "_blank" class='sys-link-normal' href = "http://www.microsoft.com/windowsserversystem/sus"> http://www.microsoft.com/windowsserversystem/sus</a><br /><br />
